    "summary": "BUSINESS ETHICS,  TRANSPARENCY, INTEGRITY AND COMPLIANCE\n\nIf we put the words \u201cbusiness ethics\u201d into the Google search engine on the Internet, we come up with more than 277.000.000 hits in just 0.53 of a second. \n\nSimply put, learning what is right or wrong, and then doing the right thing is not that simple. Most ethical dilemmas in the workplace are not simply a matter of black and white or 'just follow the rules'. \n\nRegulations are mostly static while our business environments are very dynamic. Making the rights choices is an 'art of acrobatism'.\n\nIn todays era of fundamental change, values that were previously taken for granted are now strongly questioned. Many of these values are no longer followed or even not valid anymore. As a consequence, there is no clear moral compass to guide leaders through complex dilemmas about what is right or wrong. \n\nPerhaps most important, attention to ethics in the workplaces helps ensure that when leaders and managers are struggling in times of crises and confusion, they retain a strong moral compass. \n",
